The All Progressives Congress (APC) has mourned the death of immediate past National Vice Chairman (North West), Inuwa Abdulkadir. APC said it has lost a grassroots politician, true progressive and distinguished personality who served the party and country meritoriously. The spokesman, Yekini Nabena, urged all “to remember and be comforted by the positive impact and indelible strides” of the deceased. “We express our deep condolences to his immediate family, the Sokoto sultanate, the government and people of Sokoto State. May Almighty Allah be merciful and grant him Aljanat Firdaus.” Abdulkadir, 54, passed away Monday morning at the Usmanu Danfodiyo University Teaching Hospital. He was the Chairman of the Governing Council of the National Food Drugs Administration and Control (NAFDAC). The deceased was a former Attorney General of Sokoto State. He was also the Chairman and Pro-Chancellor of Sokoto State University. Abdulkadir is survived by two wives and nine children.